  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This unit evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The intended use scope — predicting NIH index under steady-state VAD operating conditions at 2500–5000 RPM and 3–7 L/min flow — is described in the bound requirement and claim nodes. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed; all 13 credibility factors were assessed against MRL-5 thresholds. Decision: Accepted with documented residual gaps.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-cfd-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-predicts-nih-index-class3",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-benchmark-dataset"
  ],
